NAME
    CGI::Session::ID::crypt_openssl - CGI::Session ID driver for generating
    IDs based on Crypt::OpenSSL::Random

VERSION
    Version 1.00

SYNOPSIS
        use CGI::Session;
        $session = new CGI::Session('id:crypt_openssl', undef);

DESCRIPTION
    Use this module to generate hexadecimal IDs generated with
    Crypt::OpenSSL::Random for CGI::Session objects. This library does not
    require any arguments. Use this module to generate security IDs with a
    high level of randomnes.

